    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Cutibacterium Acnes Oligopeptide-2 is a single chain protein synthetically produced to be identical to a portion of the protein, Methionine ABC Transporter Substrate-Binding Protein, which is found in the bacteria, Cutibacterium acnes. The peptide contains 13 amino acids. The parent protein, Methionine ABC Transporter Substrate-Binding Protein, contains a maximum of 320 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
